    "dynamic_rich_text_kp7fCG": {
      "type": "dynamic-rich-text",
      "name": "t:sections.rich_text.presets.rich_text.name",
      "settings": {
        "width": "full-width",
        "title": "",
        "text": "<h2>Ambulance Sirens FAQs</h2><h3>Q1: What is the purpose of an ambulance siren?</h3><p>An ambulance siren alerts other drivers and pedestrians that an emergency vehicle is approaching, helping to clear the road and reduce response time.</p><h3>Q2: How loud is an ambulance siren?</h3><p>Most ambulance sirens range from 110 to 120 decibels, which is loud enough to be heard over traffic and ambient noise.</p><h3>Q3:What are the different types of ambulance siren tones?</h3><p>Common tones include Wail, Yelp, Hi-Lo, and Airhorn—each used for different traffic conditions and levels of urgency.</p><h3>Q4 Are ambulance sirens legal to use on personal vehicles?</h3><p>No, ambulance sirens are restricted to authorized emergency vehicles. Using them on a personal vehicle is illegal in most jurisdictions.</p><h3>Q5: Can I install an ambulance siren myself?</h3><p>Yes, if you're experienced with vehicle electronics, but professional installation is recommended to ensure proper performance and legal compliance.</p><h3>Q6: Do ambulance sirens come with PA systems?</h3><p>Many modern sirens include a built-in public address (PA) system for clear voice communication outside the vehicle.</p><h3>Q7: What’s the difference between 100-watt and 200-watt sirens?</h3><p>200-watt sirens are louder and more powerful, often used in larger or noisier urban areas, while 100-watt systems are standard for most EMS vehicles.</p><h3>Q8: How do I choose the right ambulance siren for my vehicle?</h3><p>Consider factors like decibel output, tone variety, size, control unit compatibility, and regulatory requirements in your area.</p><h3>Q9: Do ambulance sirens need to be synchronized with emergency lights?</h3><p>While not required, synchronizing sirens with lights improves visibility and can be beneficial in high-traffic areas.</p><h3>Q10: Where can I buy high-quality ambulance sirens online? </h3><p>You can find top-rated ambulance sirens, speakers, and accessories at<a href=\"https://www.strobesnmore.com\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Strobes N More</span></a>, trusted by first responders nationwide.</p>",
        "heading_size": "medium",
        "text_alignment": "left"
      }
    },
